📘 Data Catalog – Gold Layer
📊 Overview

The Gold Layer represents the business-ready data model designed for analytics and reporting.
It contains dimension tables and fact tables that support business intelligence, dashboards, and analytical queries.

The Gold Layer in this project contains the following tables:

gold.dim_customers

gold.dim_products

gold.fact_sales

🧑‍💼 1. gold.dim_customers
Purpose

The Customer Dimension stores enriched customer information including demographic and geographic attributes.
It provides a unified view of customers by combining CRM and ERP data sources.

| Column Name     | Data Type    | Description                                              |
| --------------- | ------------ | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| customer_key    | INT          | Surrogate key uniquely identifying each customer record. |
| customer_id     | INT          | Unique numerical identifier assigned to each customer.   |
| customer_number | NVARCHAR(50) | Business identifier representing the customer.           |
| first_name      | NVARCHAR(50) | Customer's first name.                                   |
| last_name       | NVARCHAR(50) | Customer's last name.                                    |
| country         | NVARCHAR(50) | Country where the customer resides.                      |
| marital_status  | NVARCHAR(50) | Marital status of the customer (e.g., Married, Single).  |
| gender          | NVARCHAR(50) | Gender of the customer (Male, Female, n/a).              |
| birthdate       | DATE         | Customer's date of birth.                                |
| create_date     | DATE         | Date when the customer record was created in the system. |

📦 2. gold.dim_products
Purpose

The Product Dimension contains descriptive attributes about products including their category, cost, and classification.
It enables product-level analysis for sales and reporting.

| Column Name          | Data Type    | Description                                                  |
| -------------------- | ------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| product_key          | INT          | Surrogate key uniquely identifying each product.             |
| product_id           | INT          | Internal identifier assigned to the product.                 |
| product_number       | NVARCHAR(50) | Product business code used for tracking.                     |
| product_name         | NVARCHAR(50) | Descriptive name of the product.                             |
| category_id          | NVARCHAR(50) | Identifier linking to the product category.                  |
| category             | NVARCHAR(50) | High-level product classification (e.g., Bikes, Components). |
| subcategory          | NVARCHAR(50) | Detailed classification within a category.                   |
| maintenance_required | NVARCHAR(50) | Indicates if maintenance is required (Yes/No).               |
| cost                 | INT          | Base cost of the product.                                    |
| product_line         | NVARCHAR(50) | Product line classification (e.g., Road, Mountain).          |
| start_date           | DATE         | Date when the product became available.                      |


💰 3. gold.fact_sales
Purpose

The Sales Fact Table stores transactional sales data.
It links customers and products to sales events and supports business metrics like revenue and sales volume.

| Column Name   | Data Type    | Description                                |
| ------------- | ------------ | ------------------------------------------ |
| order_number  | NVARCHAR(50) | Unique identifier for each sales order.    |
| product_key   | INT          | Foreign key referencing **dim_products**.  |
| customer_key  | INT          | Foreign key referencing **dim_customers**. |
| order_date    | DATE         | Date when the order was placed.            |
| shipping_date | DATE         | Date when the order was shipped.           |
| due_date      | DATE         | Payment due date.                          |
| sales_amount  | INT          | Total sales value of the order line.       |
| quantity      | INT          | Number of product units sold.              |
| price         | INT          | Price per product unit.                    |



⭐ Star Schema Relationship

The Gold Layer follows a Star Schema design:

            dim_customers
                  |
                  |
dim_products ---- fact_sales

fact_sales is the central table containing transactional data.

dim_customers and dim_products provide descriptive attributes.

This design enables efficient analytical queries, BI dashboards, and reporting.
















